arlut.csd.ganymede.common
Class DumpResult

java.lang.Object
  arlut.csd.ganymede.common.DumpResult
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable, java.util.Collection, java.util.List
public class DumpResult
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.util.List

This class is a serializable transport object, used to transmit the results of a data dump query to the client. DumpResult objects are created by the DumpResultBuilder factory class. The way it works is that DumpResultBuilder creates the DumpResult objects, which is transmitted through RMI to the client. The client can then call the various accessor methods to access the serialized query results. DumpResult encodes a list of field headers by name, a list of field types encoded as Shorts coded with the values enumerated in the FieldType interface, and a list of object rows, each of which contains a Vector of encoded field values. Field values are encoded as follows: Date fields as Date objects Float fields as Double objects Numeric fields as Integer objects
And Strings for everything else. The GUI client uses this object to generate its query result tables.. Later Note: Yes, I know how utterly horrifying this is. It's something I did very early on during development, and it worked well for high speed data dumping, so I just kept it. Mea culpa, mea maxima culpa. Yet, it works.

Method Detail

getHeaders

public java.util.Vector getHeaders()
This method can be called on the client to obtain a Vector of field names, used to generate the list of column headers in the GUI client. Note: The Vector returned is "live", and should not be modified by the caller, at the risk of surprising behavior.

getHeaderObjects

public java.util.Vector getHeaderObjects()
This method can be called on the client to obtain an independent Vector of DumpResultCol objects, which define the field name, field id, and field type for each column in this DumpResult. Note: The Vector returned is "live", and should not be modified by the caller, at the risk of surprising behavior.

getFieldName

public java.lang.String getFieldName(int col)
Returns the name of the field encoded in column col of the DumpResult.

getFieldId

public short getFieldId(int col)
Returns the field code for the field encoded in column col of the DumpResult.

getFieldType

public short getFieldType(int col)
Returns the field type for the field encoded in column col of the DumpResult. The field type returned is to be interpreted according to the values enumerated in the FieldType interface.

getInvids

public java.util.Vector getInvids()
This method can be called on the client to obtain a Vector of Invids, identifying the objects that are being returned in the DumpResult. Note: The Vector returned is "live", and should not be modified by the caller, at the risk of surprising behavior.

getInvid

public Invid getInvid(int row)
This method can be called on the client to obtain the object identifier Invid for a given result row.

getRows

public java.util.Vector getRows()
This method can be called on the client to obtain a Vector of Vectors, each of which contains the data values returned for each object, in field order matching the field names and types returned by getHeaders() and getHeaderObjects(). Note: The Vector returned is "live", and should not be modified by the caller, at the risk of surprising behavior.

getFieldRow

public java.util.Vector getFieldRow(int rowNumber)
This method can be called on the client to obtain a Vector containing the data values returned for the object at row row, in field order matching the field names and types returned by getHeaders() and getHeaderObjects().

getResult

public java.lang.Object getResult(int row,
                                  int col)
This method can be called on the client to obtain an Object encoding the result value for the colth field in the rowth object. These Objects may be a Double for Float fields, an Integer for Numeric fields, a Date for Date fields, or a String for other fields.

resultSize

public int resultSize()
This method can be called on the client to determine the number of objects encoded in this DumpResult.

checkBuffer

private void checkBuffer()
This method takes care of deserializing the StringBuffer we contain, to crack out the data we are interested in conveying.

dissociate

public void dissociate()
This method breaks apart the data structures held by this DumpResult.. it is intended to speed garbage collection when the contents of this DumpResult buffer have been processed and are no longer needed on the client.
